A million pounds worth of luxury seaside chalets have been demolished after being condemned by a series of huge landslides.

The devastated owners were told by the local authority that the area was unsafe and had to salvage their belongings before bulldozers were brought in to level the chalets at Monmouth Beach in Lyme Regis, Dorset.

Each hut is worth about £70,000 but due to the seaside location and stunning coastal views, their sell-on value is between £175,000 to £200,000.

