Lyme Regis Town Council, which owns the land, announced it will not renew the licences for 11 of the chalets.

One owner, speaking at the time, said: 'Some people are covered by insurance and some are not. Luckily for us our property is.

'We are only allowed to insure it up to £70,000. The total value of ours was £200,000 so the rest of the value is the location and the ongoing licence.

